Place chicken in shallow baking pan; brush with 1 tablespoon pesto. Bake at 350 degrees F for 20 minutes. Cut into 1-inch pieces and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon Morton(R) Kosher Salt; keep warm. Cook pasta according to package directions with 1 teaspoon Morton(R) Kosher Salt; add escarole to pasta during last 2 minutes of cooking time. Drain pasta and escarole reserving 1/2 cup pasta liquid. Combine pasta liquid with remaining two (2) tablespoons pesto and Morton Kosher Salt/garlic mixture.* Toss with pasta/escarole mixture, and chicken. Spoon half of mixture into 13x9x2-inch casserole dish; top with 3/4 cup shredded cheese. Spoon remaining pasta evenly over cheese layer; top with remaining 3/4 cup cheese. Bake at 350 degrees F for 15 minutes or until cheese melts and top is light golden brown. Serve immediately.